+## Implementation addendum — 2026-05-27 (IMPLEMENTED)
+
+All 5 tasks are now built and the suite is green. Verified on Node v24.12.0.
+
+| # | Task | Status | Evidence |
+|---|------|--------|----------|
+| 1 | Wire test runner | ✅ Done | `tsx@^4.22.3` added; `"test": "node --import tsx --test \"src/**/*.test.ts\""` in `package.json` |
+| 2 | `format.ts` unit tests | ✅ Done | `src/lib/format.test.ts` — 18 tests; asserts U+2212 minus, half-expand rounding (`1.005 → $1.01`), `-0`, NaN, large values |
+| 3 | Extract `rankDelta()` | ✅ Done | `src/features/rankings/rank.ts` (`rankDelta` + `formatRankDelta`); `KeywordTable.tsx` refactored to consume it |
+| 4 | `rankDelta` tests + drop-defect fix | ✅ Done | `src/features/rankings/rank.test.ts` — 9 tests; drops now render `↓ N` (red), with a regression guard asserting drops never collapse to `—` |
+| 5 | NaN-guard decision | ✅ Decided | **Resolved:** `format.ts` NaN behavior is *pinned, not changed* (tests document `$NaN`/`NaN%` leak — a UI guard is deferred to avoid altering money display without product input). New code `rankDelta` *is* guarded: non-finite → `flat`/0. |
+
+- **Suite result:** 27 tests, 27 pass, 0 fail, ~260 ms. `tsc --noEmit` clean.
+- **Behavioral change shipped:** any keyword row where `now > prev` (a rank drop)
+  now renders `↓ N` in `text-danger` instead of `—`. No such row exists in the
+  current mock `data.ts`, so the live dashboard is visually unchanged today; the
+  fix is latent-correct and covered by a regression test.
+- **No longer UNVERIFIED:** glob test-runner support confirmed working on Node 24.
